TRIO COMMITS TO CAL LUTHERAN 
Three high school basketball players said Wednesday that they have made oral 
commitments to play for Cal Lutheran. 
They are: Hank Hou, a 5-foot-10 guard from Marshall High who averaged more than 
18 points a game and was a three-year starter. 
Kevin Richberg, a 6-2 guard who averaged 15 points and was first team 
all-league for Moreau High in the Bay Area. 
Joe Cohen (6-4), a two-year varsity starter for Woodbridge High in Irvine. 
